-- Marchionne Sees Continued Weak European Car Sales in First Quarter of 2011
-- B y   J e r r o l d   C o l t e n   a n d   T o m m a s o   E b h a r d t
-- 2010-10-01T07:13:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/marchionne-sees-continued-weak-european-car-sales-in-first-quarter-of-2011.html
Fiat SpA expects the first quarter of
next year to continue to be weak for car sales in Italy and the
rest of the European Union, Chief Executive Officer Sergio
Marchionne told reporters at the Paris Auto Show today. He said
the first quarter is likely to be the weakest during the year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jerrold Colten at 
 jcolten@bloomberg.net  